Step1: Chose the Subscribtion and right Resourcegroup

Step2: Enter the Virtual Machine Name and Chose the Region of your Vm

Step3: Now you can chose the Availability options "Availability Set"

Step4: Now the Availability Set 
       * Enter the Availability Set name
       * And chose Fault domains size "2"
       * update domains size is like a "5"

Step5: chose windows VM "windows server 2019 Datacenter-*64 Gen2"

Step6: And chose Vm size is "Standard_B2ms"

Step7: Now you can Enter the VM username & Password in Administaor section

Step8: Under Networking option there is a option loadbalancing now create it
       * enter the Load balancer name and leave it rest of things default like a
            * Load balancer type is public
            * protocal is TCP
            * frontend port is "80"
            * Backend port is "80"

